message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Securing Agentic Architectures: A Deliberately Vulnerable Multi-Agent LLM Testbed"
abstract: >-
  Experimental prototype accompanying the master's thesis "Securing Agentic
  Architectures" (TU Wien). A deliberately vulnerable three-agent LLM system
  with seven attack scenarios (memory poisoning, indirect injection, cross-agent
  propagation, planner hijacking, system prompt extraction, memory membership
  probing, and tool result poisoning) and five defences (canary tokens, intent
  anchoring, counterfactual plan diffing, output spotlighting, and a provenance-based
  trust hierarchy), evaluated across fourteen models (six paid API models across
  three vendors --- OpenAI, Anthropic, and DeepSeek --- and eight free local
  open-weight models).
type: software
